# Shipyard — AI Coding Instructions

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
- Supabase (database)
- Vercel (deployment)
- npm (package manager)

## Coding Style
- Pragmatic: functional for utils, components for UI
- No over-engineering or speculative abstractions
- Minimal comments — only where logic isn't self-evident
- Server Components by default, 'use client' only when needed

## Conventions
- All pages fetching from Supabase use `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'`
- Next.js 15+ async patterns: await params/searchParams
- Dark nautical theme throughout (navy bg, slate borders, brass accents)
- Projects = Ships, Build = Under Construction, Ship = Launched, Stalled = In Drydock
